Vasota Fort and Ajinkyatara Fort from Mumbai

Trekking, Boating & Camping | Bhatkya Trekkers

Vasota Fort (Vyaghragad) Trek, Boating & Camping

Location: Near Bamnoli Village in Satara district, inside Koyna Wildlife Sanctuary.

Altitude: ~3,814 ft above sea level.

Attraction: Also known as Vyaghragad the tiger fort named by Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj due to its tough natural defenses. The fort is mostly in ruins now, but the wild jungle setting and water surrounds make it a classic adventure trek.

Trek Grade: Moderate

Boat Ride

To start the trek, you boat from Bamnoli across the Shivsagar/Koyna backwaters.

This scenic lake crossing is one of the highlights especially at sunrise or sunset.

Jungle Trek

Trail is forest and jungle terrain, roughly 56 km one way to the fort base.

Moderate difficulty good for beginners with decent fitness.

Expect dense canopy, birdlife, and views over hills and valleys.

Camping

Typical experiences include tent stays, campfire evenings, homemade meals, and starry nights.

Fun Activities, Musical Night, Party Vibe

Ajinkyatara Fort Historic Hill Fort near Satara

Location: On Ajinkyatara Mountain, overlooking Satara City, Maharashtra.

Altitude: ~3,300 ft (about 1,000 m) above sea level.

Attraction: Means Invincible Star named to reflect its strategic significance in Maratha history. Built in the 12th century by Shilahara rulers and later became important for the Marathas. Captured by Shivaji Maharaj in the 1600s and played a role in Maratha defence against Mughals and later the British. It was once part of the Maratha Empires heritage and strategy.

Trek Grade: Easy
